president fidel castro of cuba said saturday 
that he hopes presidentelect george bush will be more pragmatic 
than his predecessor in recognizing latin american realities 
its always better to deal with a pragmatic man than to deal 
with a man like president reagan who has a mind from the last 
century if that doesnt offend the last century said castro at a 
news conference 
but he said he he could not speculate on any changes in the 
abrasive relationship between the united states and communist cuba 
under the new bush administration 
they say bush is more pragmatic and less ideological than 
reagan said castro but well have to see what happens and how 
the new administration behaves 
castro said his visit here for the inauguration of carlos salinas 
de gortari as president of mexico is a sign that the united states 
longterm policy of isolating cuba has fallen apart 
thirty years have gone by and were still here he said 
castros forces overthrew the dictatorship of fulgencio batista on 
