<TEXT>
the elevation of john sununu and george 
mitchell two american politicians of partial lebanese heritage 
has instilled pride in arabamericans wherever they congregate from 
the docks of seattle and assembly lines of detroit to the halls of 
academia and the conference rooms of washington 
the process of exclusion that we suffered is now broken said 
james zogby executive director of the lobbying group arab american 
institute as he welcomed the election of democrat mitchell as senate 
majority leader and the selection by presidentelect george bush of 
republican sununu as his white house chief of staff sununus term 
as governor of new hampshire ends in early january 
weve managed to remove the taint attached to us and mature as 
a community much like the hispanics and asians said zogby 
unlike hispanics asians and other minorities the estimated 25 
million arabamericans carry the burden of antipathy toward their 
ethnic group attitudes toward them have been affected by the 
arabisraeli conflict and the strong support israel enjoys in 
congress 
sununu whose grandfather was lebanese and who has been active in 
the national association of arab americans learned this political 
lesson the hard way 
his selection by bush drew anxious reactions from the jewish 
community because of his refusal to endorse a proclamation 
condemning a united nations resolution that pronounced israel a 
racist country among the nations 50 governors sununu was the only 
one to take that stand he argued such issues were not within a 
governors domain 
sununu apologized at a news conference in washington after his 
selection by bush saying he should have signed the petition he 
later met with jewish leaders to reassure them of his support for 
israel 
he has long been aware of the pitfalls of public proarab stands 
at a keynote address to the 1984 convention of the naaa which 
adopted a resolution calling for a cutoff of american aid to israel 
he exhorted the participants to engage in political activity to 
mimic the opposition 
without naming the powerful proisrael lobby sununu talked about 
others with perspectives very different from us who have 
influenced the decisionmaking process in this country to the 
detriment of this nations foreign policy 
but he did not go beyond that an example arabamerican leaders 
say of the caution he has found it prudent to exercise 
thats how he and mitchell got where they are said james 
abourezk a former democratic senator from south dakota who is of 
arab parentage he heads the americanarab antidiscrimination 
committee 
mitchell was supported by jewish voters in maine in his 1982 and 
1988 senate races but he has also been quietly involved in arab 
causes such as the american task force on lebanon arabamerican 
organizations rallied behind his candidacy for the senate leadership 
post 
the task force in which sununu was also active is composed of 
american businessmen and politicians seeking to promote a peaceful 
solution to lebanons crisis and foster economic rehabilitation for 
the shattered country 
people of lebanese descent constitute the largest group of 
arabamericans their forebears began migrating here at the turn of 
the century 
sununu and mitchell arent alone rep mary rose oakar dohio 
also of lebanese descent is running for the chairmanship of the 
house democratic caucus 
dozens of arabamericans hold federal state and mayoral offices 
around the country among them eva sayegh tieg virginias 
secretary of human services tommy hazouri the mayor of 
jacksonville fla antony solomon state treasurer of rhode island 
michael baroody assistant secretary of labor in the reagan 
administration 
theyre openly identifying themselves as arabamericans said 
zogby whereas a few years ago they wouldnt have mentioned it at 
all 
jesse jackson the first black leader to make a serious run for 
the presidency gave arabamericans a prominent role in his campaign 
and championed one of their causes the creation of a palestinian 
homeland 
the recent political successes of arabamericans have come from 
the political mainstream rather than the fringe sununu is a 
conservative with impeccable republican credentials mitchell is an 
integral part of the political and social establishment often 
riding with bush on his airplane from washington to their homes in 
maine 
in recent years arabamericans have been organizing in labor 
unions as an ethnic group yemenite longshoremen in the west coast 
port of seattle lebanese shiite autoworkers in detroit and syrian 
steelworkers in pennsylvania 
they point with pride to such prominent americans as beverly 
hills disc jockey casey kasem and consumer advocate ralph nader 
theres a growing desire of arabamericans to identify with 
their heritage said faris bouhafa spokesman of the arabamerican 
antidiscrimination committee a civil rights and lobbying group 
for too long arabs were stereotyped and tainted in this 
country now were pointing to our past with pride teaching our 
children arabic he said 
besides providing a morale boost to the arabamerican community 
its leaders hope their political successes will help change what 
they view as a skewed us policy in the middle east 
sununu and mitchell will be less susceptible to the 
heavyhanded tactics of the proisrael lobby said bouhafa 
but former sen abourezk cautioned that both men may be too 
politically vulnerable to publicly adopt proarab stands whatever 
they may believe in their hearts 
