distort farm trade ran into heavy opposition sunday on the eve of 
freetrade talks among more than 100 nations 
the conflict over farm trade threatened to block progress on a 
wide range of other issues on the us agenda from trade in 
services to protection of intellectual property 
trade ministers are meeting here to give a political push to 
negotiations at the midpoint of the fouryear uruguay round of 
freetrade talks they are the biggest and most ambitious of the 
eight rounds that have been held since the formation of the general 
agreement on tariffs and trade after world war ii 
the european economic community which is considered the biggest 
offender in the expensive area of farm supports repeated on sunday 
its opposition to a total elimination of tradedistorting subsidies 
canadian trade minister david crosbie characterized both the 
american and the european stands as extreme 
if americans expect progress on intellectual property and 
services without achieving an accord on farm trade theyre in for 
a shock said michael duffy minister for trade negotiations for 
australia duffy said that unless things change he expected a 
stalemate that will sour the rest of the round 
australia leads the 13nation cairns group which favors 
immediate steps to reduce farm subsidies as a way to avoid an 
impasse between the us and eec positions 
but possibly preparing for a stalemate the director general of 
gatt said the talks that formally begin monday could be regarded as 
a success even if they fail to produce agreement on certain 
contentious issues 
this weeks talks could at least stop the hideandseek game 
by nailing down areas of disagreement and setting an agenda for 
negotiations over the next two years arthur dunkel the gatt chief 
said in a news conference sunday 
the united states has encountered opposition from some developing 
countries to the two other main items on its agenda free trade in 
services such as banking insurance and legal services and better 
international protection of intellectual property such as patents 
and copyrights 
agreement is considered almost assured on other areas such as 
speeding up and strengthening gatts method of resolving disputes 
and linking gatt to other international bodies such as the world 
bank and international monetary fund 
dunkels comment seemed intended in part to prepare public 
opinion for the possibility that the montreal talks will end with 
wide gaps remaining over vital issues 
the comment also dovetailed with statements by us negotiators 
who have said they would rather leave montreal with no agreement 
than with a bad agreement on vital issues 
a sloppy compromise the americans say would only make it more 
difficult to achieve progress in the remaining two years of the 
uruguay round 
the gatt midterm review includes representatives of 105 
countries including 96 member nations of the gatt 
the united states estimates that worldwide farm subsidies cost 
200 billion a year 
the 12nation eec or common market has said it is willing to 
roll back subsidies but because of intense pressure from its 11 
million farmers the eec has been unwilling to agree to their total 
elimination 
the american option is a nonstarter frans andriessen eec 
agriculture commissioner said in a news conference sunday we 
will in this negotiation stick to our basic principle 
the current uruguay round of talks began in punta del este 
uruguay in 1986 and is scheduled to end in 1990 
the gatt is both an agreement and an organization which has a 
permanent headquarters in geneva 
the talks are taking place as usual largely behind closed 
doors they are expected to last until thursday 
